AllLife Credit Card Customer Segmentation¶

AllLife Bank wants to focus on its credit card customer base in the next financial year. They have been advised by their marketing research team, that the penetration in the market can be improved. Based on this input, the Marketing team proposes to run personalised campaigns to target new customers as well as upsell to existing customers. Another insight from the market research was that the customers perceive the support services of the back poorly. Based on this, the Operations team wants to upgrade the service delivery model, to ensure that customers queries are resolved faster. Head of Marketing and Head of Delivery both decide to reach out to the Data Science team for help

Objective¶

To identify different segments in the existing customer based on their spending patterns as well as past interaction with the bank.

Key questions to be answered -¶

  • How many different segments of customers are there?
  • How are these segments different from each other?
  • What are your recommendations to the bank on how to better market to and service these customers?

About the Dataset

  • Sl_No
  • Customer Key -- Customer unique Key
  • Avg_Credit_Limit -- Averageof credit limit for the customer.
  • Total_Credit_Cards -- Number of credit cards customer owned from the bank.
  • Total_visits_bank -- Total number of physical visits customer made with the bank.
  • Total_visits_online -- Total number of visits customer made through online.
  • Total_calls_made -- Total number of calls customer made to reach the bank.

KMeans Clustering¶

In [53]:
%time
clusters=range(1,10)
meanDistortions=[]

for k in clusters:
    model=KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    model.fit(subset_scaled_df)
    prediction=model.predict(subset_scaled_df)
    distortion=sum(np.min(cdist(subset_scaled_df, model.cluster_centers_, 'euclidean'), axis=1)) / subset_scaled_df.shape[0]
                           
    meanDistortions.append(distortion)

    print('Number of Clusters:', k, '\tAverage Distortion:', distortion)

plt.plot(clusters, meanDistortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average Distortion')
plt.title('Selecting k with the Elbow Method', fontsize=20)

sil_score = []
cluster_list = list(range(2,10))

    clusterer = KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters)
    preds = clusterer.fit_predict((subset_scaled_df))

    score = silhouette_score(subset_scaled_df, preds)

Hierarchial clustering¶

In [63]:
%time
# cophenet index is a measure of the correlation between the distance of points in feature space and distance on dendrogram
distance_metrics = [ 'euclidean','chebyshev','mahalanobis','cityblock']
linkage_methods = ['single', 'complete', 'average', 'weighted']
high_cophenet_corr = 0
high_dm_lm = [0,0]
for dm in distance_metrics:
    for lm in linkage_methods:
        Z = linkage(subset_scaled_df, metric=dm, method=lm)
        c, coph_dists = cophenet(Z , pdist(subset_scaled_df))
        print('Cophent correlation for distance metrics {} and linkage method {} is {}'.format(dm,lm,c))
        if high_cophenet_corr < c:
            high_cophenet_corr = c
            high_dm_lm[0] = dm
            high_dm_lm[1] = lm
print('Highest cophenet correlation is {}, which is obtinaed with {} distance metric and {} linkage method'.format(high_cophenet_corr ,high_dm_lm[0],high_dm_lm[1]))

# List of all linkage methods to check
methods = ['single',
           'average', 
           'complete',
           'centroid',
           'ward',
           'weighted']

# Calculate the pairwise distance form the dataset to be used in the cophenetic correlation calculation
#pw_distance = pdist(credit_scaled)

# Create lists to save results of coph calculation
compare_cols = ['Linkage', 'Cophenetic Coefficient']
compare = []

# Create a subplot image
fig, axs = plt.subplots(len(methods), 1, figsize=(15, 30))

# Enumerate through the list of all methods above
# Get linkage, plot dendrogram, calculate cophenetic coefficient
for i, method in enumerate(methods):
    
    Z = linkage(subset_scaled_df, metric='euclidean', method=method)

    dendrogram(Z, ax=axs[i]);
    axs[i].set_title(f'Dendrogram ({method.capitalize()} Linkage)')
    coph_corr, coph_dist = cophenet(Z, pdist(subset_scaled_df))
    axs[i].annotate(f'Cophenetic\nCoefficient\n{coph_corr:0.2f}', 
                    (0.80, 0.80),
                    xycoords='axes fraction')
    compare.append([method, coph_corr])
  • Observations

Dendrogram with ward linkage method shows distinct and separate cluster

Comparision between kMeans and Hierarchical clustering.¶

  • K Means clustering
    • Have the flexibility to pass the number of clusters we want to perform.
    • It helps when there is huge set of data to perform the segmentation.
    • We have to consider both elbow curve to check from where the distortion is linear and silhouette cofficients to determine the number clusters to be used to perform th efficient segmentation.
    • Through elbow curve, after 5th clusters curve is linear for the distrotion.
    • Through Silhoutte cofficients 4th cluster is having higher than the 5th clustering.
    • based on the elbow curve having 5 clusters is optimal usage of clustering with Kmeans model.
  • Hierarchical Clustering
    • Model has to run for all the cluster either by aggloromative divisive Hierarchical clustering.
    • It takes lots of time when we are dealing with huge set of data to perform 1 cluster to n(total observations) number of clusters.
    • We have to conside cophenet correlation and dendogram comparision to determine number of optimal clusters.
    • Highest cophenet correlation is 0.8859449149266504, which is obtained with euclidean distance metric and average linkage method.
    • Out of all the dendrogram we saw, it is clear that cophenet index is maximum with euclidean distance metric with average
      linkage method.
    • 4 cluster would be appropriate number of cluster from dendrogram with ward linkage method

For this problem statement, not seeing much diffeence in computation time as we are dealing with small set of data.

By comparing the Kmeans and Hierarchical clustering, prefer to go with Kmeans elbow curve with 5 clusters to get the optimal usage of clustering.

Business recommendation¶

  • Cluster 0

    • Marketing team can develop a campaign to reach out this segment to upsell the products as the customers are having very less credit limit as well as less number of credit cards with the bank.
    • Customers in this segment are making lot of calls to get the resolution for the issues, operations team has to come up with a strategy to resolve the issues with in the first or second call to improve the customer expericene.

  • Cluster 1

    • Marketing team can come up with a strategy about offering higher credit card limits by upselling the higher limit credit cards.
    • Customers in this segment are making lot of personal visits to the bank to resolve/completing thier trasactions. Operations team has to focus on what is causing the clients to make the personal visits to the bank. They have to build a strategy to improve the customer experience by making them to resolve the issues either through online portal or customer service call.

  • Cluster 2

    • Customers in this segment are having higher credit limit as well as more number of credit cards and they are the ones
      generting more revenue to the bank. Marketing team can build a strategy by about how to retain these customers by giving additional incentives on the credit cards.
    • Customers are mainly dependent on online portals to perform the transactions/resolve the issues, operations team has to focus more on how to improve the online experience by providing exhaustive information and search capabilities and for the
      customers on this segment.

  • Cluster 3

    • Marketing team can develop a campaign to reach out this segment to upsell the products as the customers are having very less credit limit as well as less number of credit cards with the bank.
    • Customers in this segment are making moderate number of calls to get the resolution for their issues, operations team has to come up with a strategy to resolve the issues with in the first or second call to improve the customer expericene.

  • Cluster 4

    • Customers in this segment are having lower credit limits but owning good number of credit cards with the bank, Marketing team has to focus on building a campaign to upsell the credit cards that has more credit limits.
    • Customers in this segment are making moderate number of personal visits to the bank to resolve the issues/complete the
      transactions. Operations team has check the past data to seek how the bank can help these customers segments to find the resolution through online or customer srvice calls instead of making personal visits to the bank. Making a personal visit to the bank is always expensie to both the customer as well as to bank.
